#1.A
find_values <- function (v){
  the_mean = mean(v)
  the_sd = sd(v)
  vec_for_sd = c()
  
  for (i in v){
    value = (i - the_mean) / the_sd
    vec_for_sd = c(vec_for_sd, value)
  }
  #return (sd(vec_for_sd))
}
find_values(c(1:100))
  1. Takes in the vector X = 1:100 and returns the values (xi - \(\overline{x}\) / s , xi + \(\overline{x}\) / s) where s is that sample standard deviation.
    Result: ( -7.522984 , 108.523 )

find_ssd <- function (vec){
  m = mean(vec)
  s = 0 
  for (i in vec){
    sum_of_vec = (i - m) ^ 2 
    s = sum_of_vec + s
  }
  
  ssd = sqrt (s / (length(vec) - 1))  #find the sample standard deviation
  
  x = m - 2*ssd
  y = m + 2*ssd
  #print (x)
  #print(y)   #prints two values  (x,y)
}

find_ssd(c(1:100))
  1. We are Finding the mean after removing any values three times the standard deviation from the mean and calculating the mean after removing said values. Test vector X = c(1:100,200,300)

remove_it <- function (vec){
   num_to_remove = 3*sd(vec) + mean (vec)  #finds values too large or too small
   new_vec = c()
   new_vec = vec[vec<= num_to_remove] #removes values 
   
   #return (mean(new_vec))       #returns the mean of the vector
}

flipCoin <- function (){
  flipTheCoin = sample (c(1,2), 20, replace = TRUE)   # 1 is heads, 2 is tails
  prob_of_heads = (sum(flipTheCoin == 1)) / length(flipTheCoin) #calculates the probability of heads
  #print (prob_of_heads)
}
flipCoin()  #calls function


#2B
val_of_n = c(10,100,1000,10000,100000) #our vector for the amount of n's
many_rolls = sapply(val_of_n, function(n){
  flipTheCoin = sample (c(1,2), 20, replace = TRUE, prob = c(1/2, 1/2))   # 1 is heads, 2 is tails
  prob_of_heads = (sum(flipTheCoin == 1)) / length(flipTheCoin) #calculates the probability of heads
  return (prob_of_heads)
  
})
names(many_rolls) = paste("n =",val_of_n,sep = "")

#4A 
total_students <- function(num){ 
  students_prob = c(1:20)  #using a random number from 1 - 20 to simulate the probability that 5% of the time a student wont turn in their HW
  pick_a_num = sample (students_prob, num, replace = TRUE) #picks a number between 1-20
  total_num = 0  #our counter for number of students successes

  for (i in pick_a_num){ #if the random number is 1 then they didnt do their HW
    if (i == 1){
      total_num = total_num + 1 #increases count by 1
    }
  }
  return (total_num)  #returns the total number of students who didnt do their HW
}

total_students(40)  #calls function

hw_not_done <- function(trials){ #you pass the number of trials you want it do, in our case 1,000,000
  n_times = sapply(1:trials,function(i){
    sucesses = c(total_students(40))    #creates a vector with the number of successes
  })
  return (n_times)
}
